# PowerShell Development Workflow

This project uses PowerShell for development commands. Reference the comprehensive command set in [scripts/dev-commands.ps1](mdc:scripts/dev-commands.ps1).

## Key Development Commands

### Project Setup
```powershell
# Navigate to project root
cd C:\Users\samne\PycharmProjects\ai_assignments

# Activate virtual environment
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

# Install dependencies
pip install -r config\requirements.txt
pip install -r config\requirements-testing.txt
```

### Testing Commands
```powershell
# Run all tests
python -m pytest tests\ -v --tb=short

# Run specific test categories
python -m pytest tests\unit\ -v --tb=short
python -m pytest tests\integration\ -v --tb=short
python -m pytest tests\e2e\ -v --tb=short --timeout=600

# Run with coverage
python -m pytest tests\ -v --cov=src --cov-report=html --cov-report=term-missing
```

### Code Quality
```powershell
# Format code
black src\ tests\
isort src\ tests\

# Lint code
flake8 src\ tests\ --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics

# Type checking
mypy src\ --ignore-missing-imports
```

### Application Launch
```powershell
# Launch Gradio app
python -m src.gradio_app.main

# Launch with MCP server
python -m src.gradio_app.main --mcp-server

# Launch with custom host/port
python -m src.gradio_app.main --host 0.0.0.0 --port 7860
```

### Cleanup Commands
```powershell
# Clean Python cache
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter "__pycache__" | Remove-Item -Recurse -Force
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter "*.pyc" | Remove-Item -Force

# Clean test artifacts
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .pytest_cache\
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .coverage
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force htmlcov\
```

## Project Structure
- **Source Code**: `src/` directory
- **Tests**: `tests/` directory (unit, integration, e2e)
- **Configuration**: `config/` directory
- **Documentation**: `docs/` directory
- **Scripts**: `scripts/` directory

Always use PowerShell commands and backslashes for Windows paths. Reference [scripts/dev-commands.ps1](mdc:scripts/dev-commands.ps1) for the complete command reference.